I felt so good after this. Centered and relaxed. 

After yoga: the moment I saw that my PC had low battery, I didn't stress and hurry to plug it in as I usually do. I calmly took the charger ... put one end in the PC ... put the other end in the plug. 

I felt good and calm after the practice, but still this really surprised me. That I with awareness could do this action, to plug in my computer, so calmly, with no worry.  That I stopped myself from giving into stress,  my body wanting - and demanding - to stay in this nice calmness that we just build. 

That was a bit of a moment to me .. to really realise what yoga can do to me .. can do for me. To move with gentleness, care and sweetness to myself - not allowing external potential stressfull situations to get to me and sweep me out of my balance, but to stay strong and connected in myself. To put myself (how I feel, how I move, my health) first, rather than giving into external stress. 

Thank you.

Early this morning as my husband got off night shift, he slipped a package under my pillow.  My new hoodie- BREATH.  I wore my hoodie to work today.  I needed to feel grounded and connected to my breath.  I wanted to take the positive energy that I am gaining from this daily practice into the everyday.  Today, I needed to connect with my team lead about some systemic problems in my department.  She looked at my hoodie and exclaimed!  Yoga with Adriene.  I'm doing a 30 day challenge right now.  I laughed and shared "me too".  Within seconds, my energy shifted.  I see us both on a journey.  We are both navigating stress.  Let us do so with grace.  We can support each other.   My default when faced with stress at work was to vacillate between the emotions of anger and apathy.  Through this practice I am expanding to a new feeling- curious.  I am starting to approach problems with curiosity.  I don't need to know the answer.  I can be curious as to the process.
Arigato!
